		>
		["en"] = <
			language = <[ISO_639-1::en]>
			purpose = <"Archetype to be used to effectively evaluate grade of depression using the MADRS or MADRS-S archetype.">
			use = <"To evaluate the presence/severity of depression based on the MADRS score.
The Montgomery-Åsberg Depression Rating Scale was developed from the Comprehensive Psychopathological Rating Scale, and consists of 10 items each yielding a score of 0 (best possible) to 6 (worst possible);

- Apparent sadness
- Reported sadness
- Inner tension
- Reduced sleep 
- Reduced appetite
- Concentration difficulties
- Lassitude
- Inability to feel
- Pessimistic thoughts
- Suicidal thoughts

Total score ranges between 0 to 60. Scores 0 to 6 = normal/symptom absent, 7 to 19 = mild depression, 20 to 34 = moderate depression, and >34 = severe depression.

The rating should be based on a clinical interview moving from broadly phrased questions about symptoms to more detailed ones which allow a precise rating of severity. The interviewer must decide whether the rating correlates to the defined scale steps (0, 2, 4, 6) or the ones between them (1, 3, 5). The items should be rated with regards to how the patient has done over the past week. ">
			keywords = <"Montgomery", "depression", "Åsberg", "rating scale">
			misuse = <"Do not use to evaluate the self-assessment scale (MADRS-S)">
			copyright = <"© Cambio Healthcare Systems">
		>
	>
